headline.main: CONFEREES FAVOR OWI DOMESTIC FUND; Branch Which House Voted to End Is Slated for $2,750,000 of $33,155,993 Approved

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, July 1 (U.P.) -- Senate and House conferees tonight compromised on a $2,750,000 appropriation for the domestic branch of the Office of War Information. The agreement virtually assured continuance, at least on a limited basis, of the domestic branch which the House previously had voted to abolish.
abstract: Sen and House conferees agree on $2,750,000 appropriation for domestic branch; NY-NJ regional offices and branches and motion-picture unit to liquidate
